The Remote XUL Manager is a tool created in response to the following Mozilla
bug: https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=595260.

This is an extension for Firefox (and potentially other applications) that
allows users to easily manage the Remote XUL domain whitelist. Enabling specific
domains where the user want to enable remote XUL.

Version 0.5 is a basic add/remove tool. Future versions will likely include more
useful tools for remote deployment.

Known limitations:
* Doesn't work with the file:// protocol.
